The paper deals with recommendation systems, which are typically studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to generate latent factor representations for new items suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract information from textual descriptions of items, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of latent factor models and matrix factorization techniques for recommendation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
